data.chText: 全神贯注的；聚精会神的；专心致志的
data.enText: so interested or involved in sth that you give it all your attention

word_means: 占去的全部注意力和时间

means: 占去(某人)的全部注意力和时间

tr: giving or marked by complete attention to
example: that engrossed look or rapt delight
so intent on this fantastic...narrative that she hardly stirred"- Walter de la Mar

tr: written formally in a large clear script, as a deed or other legal document

value.def: If you are engrossed in something, it holds your attention completely.

example.ex: Tony didn't notice because he was too engrossed in his work.
example.tran: 托尼因为太专注于自己的工作而毫未察觉。
